<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-12T00:00:00+00:00" n="111" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                </head>
                                <p>On September 29 <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> also met with <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> and the Acting New
                                    Zealand High Commissioner to discuss the Chinese onshore
                                    islands. For a memorandum of their conversation by <persName corresp="#p_BOWIERR1">Bowie</persName>, September 29, see
                                    the compilation on China in <ref target="frus1952-54v14p1">volume XIV</ref>.</p>
                            </div>
